  "text": "However, in contrast with the sine-Gordon equation, no obstruction to asymptotic stability is known at the nonlinear level so that one can hope that because of nonlinear dumping this mode goes to zero for large time (see [CITATION_1] ). This observation leads to separate the mode Y 1 at the linear level, and to study carefully quadratic terms for this mode. It also suggest that the rate of convergence to zero should be rather weak. We proceed in four steps.",
